text: thumb Tervakoski is a town in Janakkala, Finland. In 2004, there was 4750 inhabitants. A well-known and popular amusement park Puuhamaa is located in the village. Tervakoski Oy paper mill, established in 1818, is located in Tervakoski.https://www.delfortgroup.com/en/career/finland/tervakoski-oy/ ==References== == External links == * Tervakoski.fi Category:Janakkala
